This paper deals with the problem of learning graph representations via low-dimensional embeddings, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on embedding directed acyclic graphs and proposes a novel method using hyperbolic spaces and hierarchical relations viewed as partial orders. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these sub-categories are closely related to the problem addressed in the paper. Additionally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with graph representations and embeddings.
